Business must have been slow because of the heat (almost 100° today) . We were sitting for almost 5 to 10 mins before we were attended. 3 tables and 4 workers. When one of the ladies came to us and asked if we have been taken care of I told her no and that she must be the only one working and that we have been waiting for soo long. No apology. Stayed to eat because my mother was hungry. I guess that is what happens when the actual mngr or owner isn't around. Won't be going there again.

This is a great place for a hearty home made Latin meal.  Everything is always fresh and on time.  It gets busy during lunch time.  It's not a fancy place...but very clean.  Staff is super attentive and polite.  Love the chuichifrito which is hand food bites and filled with flavor.  Try the pastillios, empanadas, papa relleno (patatote ball filled with meat), the plantains filled with meat.  I personally enjoy the cold fresh house salad...simple but refreshing.  Their tropical drinks are delicious.  They also carry wine, sangria and beer.
